    <h2 class="h2">How will the panel decide which awards are made from the Street Aid fund?</h2>
    <p>The homeless person must reside in the Nottingham area (including the associated urban boroughs such as West Bridgford and Beeston).</p>
    <p>The panel must be convinced that the grant will help the homeless person avoid spending time on the streets.</p>
    <p>The referring charity must demonstrate that they have looked for alternative sources of funding or alternative sources of those goods.</p>
    <p>The panel will seek to ensure that purchases are from the most appropriate and cost effective sources.</p>
    <h2 class="h2">Who pays for Nottingham Street Aid overheads?</h2>
    <p>Running Street Aid costs money. The costs include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>A small fee to the companies who provide the text number and donation page</li>
      <li>Contactless points (graphics and lease cost)</li>
      <li>Advertising</li>
      <li>One part time worker to promote and manage the initiative</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We have been able to draw money to the scheme from the council and businesses, much of which would not otherwise have been spent. This money covers all overheads, so that all the money donated by the public (including Gift Aid) is spent on items for homeless people in Nottingham.</p>
